# Personal Website Constraints

This is a minimal personal website. Agents must follow these rules at all times.

## Technology

- **HTML and CSS only.** No JavaScript, no frameworks, no preprocessors, no build tools.
- Do not add `<script>` tags or JS files under any circumstances.
- Do not introduce Sass, Tailwind, PostCSS, or any CSS tooling.
- The only files allowed are `index.html`, `style.css`, and any static assets (images, fonts).

## Structure

The site has exactly three sections:
1. **About** — a short personal bio (user fills this in).
2. **3-Media Rule** — the user's current three active medias (one book, one series, one game — at most).
3. **Completed** — past medias with a one/two-line comment and an addition timestamp.

Do not add, remove, or rename sections without explicit instruction.

## Design

- Earth-tone palette only: linens, parchemnt, walnut, sienna, forest green, slate.
- Minimal typography: serif body font, monospace for tags and dates.
- No decorative icons, illustrations, or heavy visual elements.
- High contrast between text and background at all times.
- Keep whitespace generous and layout single-column.

## Content

- The bio in `#about` is placeholder text; leave it for the user to fill.
- Current media items in `#current` use `<span class="media-title">` — leave empty if the user has not provided a title.
- `#completed` is split into three `<div class="completed-group">` blocks, one each for books, series, and games, each with an `<h3 class="group-label {type}">` heading.
- Each completed entry needs: `.media-title`, a `<time class="completed-date">` with a `YYYY-MM-DD` date, and an italic `.completed-comment`. No per-item type tag.
